'''Conor Coventry''' (born 25 March 2000) is an Irish professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays for [[Premier League]] club [[West Ham United F.C.|West Ham United]] as a [[midfielder]].
==Club career== Coventry joined the [[West Ham United F.C. Under-23s and Academy|youth academy]] of [[West Ham United F.C.|West Ham United]] at the age of 10.<ref name="Professional contract for Hammers youngster">{{cite web |title=Professional contract for Hammers youngster |url=https://www.whufc.com/news/articles/2017/may/25-may/professional-contract-hammers-youngster |publisher=West Ham United F.C. |accessdate=27 September 2018 |date=25 May 2018}}</ref> He scored his first goal for the under-23 team on his debut on 20 February 2017, in a 2–0 victory against [[Fulham F.C. Academy|Fulham]].<ref>{{cite web |author1=Gavan Casey |title=Watch: 16-Year-Old Ireland Prospect Scores Peach On West Ham U23s Debut |url=https://www.balls.ie/football/conor-coventry-359555 |publisher=Balls |accessdate=27 September 2018 |date=21 February 2017}}</ref> During the [[2017–18 Professional U23 Development League|2017–18 season]], he played ten times in [[Professional Development League]] and four times in [[EFL Trophy]] and won the Academy Player of the Season award at the end of the season on 25 April 2018.<ref>{{cite web |title=Conor Coventry wins Dylan Tombides Award |url=https://www.whufc.com/news/articles/2018/april/25-april/conor-coventry-wins-dylan-tombides-award |publisher=West Ham United F.C. |accessdate=27 September 2018 |date=25 April 2018}}</ref>
On 25 May 2018, Coventry signed his first professional contract with the club. About it, he said "I’ve worked for this for a long time so yes, I’m really happy to sign the deal".<ref name="Professional contract for Hammers youngster"/> On 26 September, he made his first team debut, coming on as a substitute for [[Pedro Obiang]] in an 8–0 victory against [[Macclesfield Town F.C.|Macclesfield Town]] in the [[EFL Cup]].<ref>{{cite web |title=West Ham United 8 - 0 Macclesfield Town |url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/45569334 |publisher=BBC |accessdate=27 September 2018 |date=26 September 2018}}</ref>
==International career== Coventry is eligible for Ireland as his mother is Irish. Coventry has been capped by Republic of Ireland at [[Republic of Ireland national under-17 football team|under-17 level]] and made his debut for the [[Republic of Ireland national under-19 football team|under-19 team]] in 2018.<ref>{{cite web |author1=Maurice Brosnan |title=Promising Irish Youngster Called Up To West Ham Senior Squad For Pre-Season |url=https://www.balls.ie/football/promising-irish-youngster-called-west-ham-senior-squad-pre-season-392316 |publisher=Balls |accessdate=27 September 2018 |date=6 July 2018}}</ref>
